# ─── Override Linguist for language stats ─────────────────────────────────

# 1) Treat Markdown as “code” (detectable) and not just documentation
*.md   linguist-language=Markdown   linguist-detectable=true   linguist-documentation=false

# 2) (Optional) Force JSON/YAML/TOML detection if you have data/config files
# Uncomment any you need:

*.json   linguist-language=JSON
#*.yml    linguist-language=YAML
#*.yaml   linguist-language=YAML
#*.toml   linguist-language=Toml

# 3) Custom overrides for other file types
# e.g. if you want a bespoke extension to count as a real language:
#*.obsidian.json   linguist-language=JSON
#*.customext       linguist-language=MyLang

# 4) Hide or vendor non‑source files so they don’t pollute stats
# (images, assets, generated code, docs folder, etc.)
#assets/**         linguist-vendored=true
#images/**         linguist-vendored=true
#dist/**           linguist-vendored=true
#build/**          linguist-vendored=true

# 5) If you have a docs/ folder you want completely ignored
# docs/**           linguist-documentation=true
